<br>
This is false. You have the advantage of being prepared, which far outweighs the disadvantage of being solo.<br>
<br>
It's simple, you have the luxury of picking your targets and having buffs ready, full mana, health etc. Where the person you are about to pk, most likely isn't ready, isn't at full health, and does not have their buff order ready, pvp spells up, right clickies ready, etc etc.<br>
<br>
They may have engaged with a mob recently, or are about to and not expecting to be pked.<br>
<br>
Not to mention with all the zones, it's pretty easy to find someone by themselves somewhere to kill, but much harder for a group of antis to track down a few solo pkers. <br>
<br>
Even better, you can exp in completely safety now thanks to Ldon.<br>
